  <name>ElecWhat</name>
  <summary>Simple desktop WhatsApp client for Linux</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      ElecWhat is a simple and stable desktop WhatsApp client for Linux built with Electron.
      It provides a clean interface to access WhatsApp Web with additional desktop integration features.
    </p>
    <p>Features include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Desktop notifications with unread count</li>
      <li>System tray icon with AppIndicator support</li>
      <li>Custom keyboard shortcuts</li>
      <li>Custom CSS styling support</li>
      <li>Spellcheck functionality</li>
      <li>CLI and D-Bus interface for window management</li>
      <li>Preserve window position and settings</li>
      <li>Custom user scripts support</li>
      <li>Custom tray icons</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This application is very stable and lightweight, with less than 600 lines of code.
      It has been designed to be simple, reliable, and trustworthy for daily use.
    </p>
  </description>
